# API Conventions: {{ display_name }}

## Base Path

Use `/api/v1`.

## DRF Style Rules

- plural resources
- explicit serializer classes
- explicit permission classes
- predictable pagination and error envelopes

## Suggested Endpoint Shape

- `GET /api/v1/resources/`
- `POST /api/v1/resources/`
- `GET /api/v1/resources/{id}/`
- `PATCH /api/v1/resources/{id}/`
- `DELETE /api/v1/resources/{id}/`

## Error Envelope

Prefer a stable error envelope even when DRF defaults are tempting:

```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Invalid request payload",
    "details": []
  }
}
```

## Pagination

Prefer one default pagination style per service and document it clearly. Cursor pagination is usually better for growing datasets; page-number pagination is fine for internal tools with modest scale.

